    • maxBatchSize

      public final long maxBatchSize
      Batch sizes will never be bigger than this.

      public final long batchTimeoutMicros
      Maximum number of microseconds to wait before outputting an incomplete batch.

    • maxEnqueuedBatches

      public final long maxEnqueuedBatches
      Maximum number of batches enqueued. Default: 10.

    • allowedBatchSizes

      public final long[] allowedBatchSizes
      Optional list of allowed batch sizes. If left empty, does nothing. Otherwise, supplies a list of batch sizes, causing the op to pad batches up to one of those sizes. The entries must increase monotonically. If enable_large_batch_splitting is false (i.e., large-input-split is not enabled) the final entry must equal max_batch_size.

    • container

      public final String container
      Controls the scope of sharing of this batch.

    • sharedName

      public final String sharedName
      Concurrently running instances of batch in the same device with the same container and shared_name will batch their elements together. If left empty, the op name will be used as the shared name.
